{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567084","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567084"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:20+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:54:20+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18927"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18927","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18927"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.01,0.27,0.04,0.57]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11660"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80400"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11660","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11660"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18927"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65672"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"5760"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11304"},{"type":"tags","id":"11336"},{"type":"tags","id":"11337"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27436"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27437"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80400","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80400"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student observes a senior doctor failing to check a patient\u0027s allergy status before prescribing penicillin. The patient experiences an anaphylactic reaction requiring intensive care admission.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the essential elements required to establish medical negligence?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Professional misconduct, patient complaint, and disciplinary action","Written contract, breach of contract, and financial loss","Medical error, adverse outcome, and formal apology","Intent to harm, causation, and damages","Duty of care, breach of duty, and causation with harm"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe three essential elements required to establish medical negligence are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDuty of care, breach of duty, and causation with harm\u003C/strong\u003E - These form the legal foundation for negligence claims. The healthcare provider must have a duty to the patient, breach that duty by failing to meet the standard of care, and that breach must directly cause harm to the patient.\u003Cbr /\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntent to harm, causation, and damages\u003C/strong\u003E - Intent to harm is not required for negligence. Negligence can occur through carelessness or oversight\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProfessional misconduct, patient complaint, and disciplinary action\u003C/strong\u003E - These may follow negligence but are not the legal elements required to establish it\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWritten contract, breach of contract, and financial loss\u003C/strong\u003E - These relate to contract law rather than negligence law\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMedical error, adverse outcome, and formal apology\u003C/strong\u003E - While these may be present in negligence cases, they do not establish legal negligence\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn the example given, there was a duty of care to the patient, a breach of duty in failing to check allergies, and harm caused by that breach resulting in anaphylaxis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Negligence claims require proof of duty of care, breach of duty, and harm/damages caused by that breach.","Healthcare professionals have an established duty of care to their patients through the doctor-patient relationship.","The standard of care is measured against what a reasonable practitioner would do in similar circumstances."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 18]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Cheluvappa R, Selvendran S. Medical negligence - Key cases and application of legislation. Ann Med Surg (Lond). 2020 Jul 17;57:205-211. doi: 10.1016/j.amsu.2020.07.017. PMID: 32793340; PMCID: PMC7413923. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7413923/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65672"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18927"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65672","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65672"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T16:02:44+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T16:03:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11660"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80400"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null